  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Sub-National Hum. Coord</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to achieve amongst other objectives to Strengthening Capacity and Coordination as well as ensure accountability and transparency in humanitarian activities in Benue State. This is because there are gaps especially at the state level andacross the state on how disasters are managed, and lapses in coordination when disaster occurs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="24">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">JUSTICE DEVELOPMENT and  PEACE/CARI</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Justice, Development, Peace and Caritas Commission, Catholic Diocese of Otukpo, Benue State, is a faith based organization established in 1997 by the Catholic Bishop of the Catholic Diocese of Otukpo. The Catholic Diocese of Otukpo Benue State is registered with the Cooperate Affairs Commission,the commission works assiduously with other stakeholders to advocate and champion for social systems and structures that will foster the reign of Justice, Love and Peace where the dignity and rights of the human person are upheld, option for the poor a priority and ideals of self reliance and transparency are promoted for accelerated integral development ofthe human person.
Founded in July, 2005, JDPC was formed to serve as the coordinating body to respond to the needs of victims of natural and man-made disasters in Benue  State. The initial design also incorporated 4 additional States in the capacity building training namely: - Kano, Kaduna, Bauchi and Benue States. This programme has since 2005 responded to the needs of over 100,000 Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) as well as victims of natural disasters in the state irrespective of creed, religion or tribe.

Our activities include: -
# Assessment, Registration of IDPs and Relief intervention
# Rehabilitation and Re-settlement
# Advocacy Visits to Key Religious, Traditional, Community Leaders and Security Personnel
# Networking and building strategic partnerships
# Capacity Building of Humanitarian Actors
# Formation of Peace Clubs in Secondary Schools
# Implementing programmes and projects with communitiesto improve their livelihoods
# Monitoring and evaluation of programme activities
# Implementing a multi-partner project aimed at commercializing cassava seed production and increasing farmer purchase of high quality cassava seed of improved variety
# Strengthening linkages in the cassava value chain.</narrative>
  </participating-org>
